Would you be ok if we closed this ticket out now while we focus on the Netapp issues, or is there any other questions remaining around the upgrade I can help with?

Hello Bradley,

Thank you for taking the time to meet today.

Today we:
Looked into the certificate errors you were seeing in the FSAA scan.
We also looked into the errors that were being thrown by the Sharepoint scans.
I was able to speak with our internal teams and they have confirmed what we were speaking about, this should be a warning and not an error.

At this point I will be opening a new ticket to open up a change request to get this fixed in future versions to make sure its labeled as a warning and not an error. You don't need to do anything on that ticket as it is only going to exist to make the change request and it will be closed immediately after I get a request number.

As for this case, since the scans seem to be working, if you have no objections I'd like to close the upgrade ticket as there are no outstanding issues relating to the upgrade unless you have any other questions about it.


Our next steps are:
I will:
Open a ticket to ask for the change request on the error labeling.



Thank you,
Ian Ranstrom
Senior Technical Support Engineer
